The paper focuses on exploring the memorability of spatial scientific visualizations, which involves analyzing the visual features that contribute to memorability. This suggests a strong emphasis on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves curating and analyzing a large dataset of scientific visualization images, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves sentiment analysis, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
